Birthday presents came in early for Tarak from his Mumma ❤️

Please notice how she gave me my outfit 😂

When your asked to describe a mother, they are often described as Sacrificers. 
The one who who puts her dreams, aspiration,herself on hold for her family. 
The one whose life is controlled, criticised, opinions past by people she knows and doesn’t know.
To one whose opinions, feelings are not validate or even looked at.
A Mother is often made to believe that it is her duty to put herself last. 

We need to stop that narrative!

“What would I say?”- Pieces of advice from women who are changing the narrative. 

Being a mother is ONE of the many roles you play. You are allowed to have other roles- wife, daughter, sister, friend, entrepreneur, boss, chief minister, teacher, doctor etc 

YOU ARE ALLOWED to have a life outside looking after your children.
YOU ARE ALLOWED to be your own person.
YOU ARE ALLOWED to look after yourself- physically, mentally, spiritually. 
YOU ARE ALLOWED to be self centred.
YOU ARE ALLOWED to follow your dreams.
YOU ARE ALLOWED TO BE YOU! 

It’s not selfish to love yourself , take care of yourself and to make your happiness a priority. It is necessary! 
Be someone who makes yourself happy and confident! 

I have had the privilege to work on this little project for today with SO many lovely mamas, boss ladies and powerhouses. 

Happy Mothers Day 💓

latestPosts.caption:
🧱 Think theme parks are just for big kids? Think again — @legolandmalaysia is a brick-tastic blast for toddlers and grown-ups alike! 🌈👨‍👩‍👧‍👦

From pint-sized play zones to splash-tastic water rides and thrilling rollercoasters, Legoland Malaysia has something for every kind of kid — and every kind of parent! 💦🎢🎠
We checked into the Kingdom-themed hotel (10/10 for magic), tackled room scavenger hunts, explored the Sea Life Aquarium 🐠🐧 — and still had energy for the entire park… even in the rain!
Also, the food? Shockingly good. 🍲
The staff? Incredibly kind.
The whole experience? Absolutely worth the hype.

And did you know? It’s just a wee wind from Singapore — only a 1-hour drive and you’re there! ✨🛣️

Bookmark this for your next family getaway and tag your travel buddy — because every family deserves a trip this fun (and this easy)!
.

.

.

latestPosts.caption:
🧱 It’s not just a theme park… it’s a LEGO dream come true! 🇲🇾
— Day 1 of our @legolandmalaysia adventure!

From the moment we checked into our Kingdom-themed room, the magic began. There was even a scavenger hunt inside the room that kept the kids buzzing with excitement! Despite the rain, we powered through the entire Legoland Park—and had a blast on every ride. ☔️🎢

What truly surprised us? The food! Usually resort food is a miss, but here—from Indian to Continental—it was absolutely delicious. 🍽️✨

Everything is thoughtfully designed for children—from mini cutlery stands and self-serve stations to tiny robes, slippers, and even a child-height sink. It’s not just kid-friendly, it’s kid-empowering. 💛

This is just Day 1 of our family vlog series, and we’re already blown away.
📍Follow us for Day 2 tomorrow—there’s so much more LEGO magic to come! 🧳🎥👨‍👩‍👧‍👦

.

.

.

latestPosts.caption:
Happy 7th Birthday, my Taru. My 7 on 7th. 💫
The moment I saw those two lines, I knew life would never be the same—and I was right. You changed everything… for the better.
The day I held you in my arms, my heart chose to walk outside my body—on your side—for the rest of my life. 💛
There aren’t enough words to explain how much I love you, but I promise you this: you will always feel it.
I love the way you dance, the way you kick that football, your jokes, your curiosity, your endless questions.
You’re funny, smart, kind, and wonderfully you.
No matter how old you grow, you’ll always be my baby.
You and I share something special—something only we can understand.
Thank you for choosing me.
Shine bright. Be kind. Stay you.
I love you more than anything in the world. Happy Birthday, my love. 💙🌟

Sometimes, the world writes your script before you’ve even spoken.
You carry someone else’s silence.
You’re blamed for someone else’s choice.
You’re shamed for things that happened around you — not because of you.

And somehow, no one ever stops to ask your version of the truth.
They just decide. Assume. Cancel.

But here’s the thing:
Not everyone gets to tell their side.
And some stories were never ours to tell.

So instead of judgment… what if we chose curiosity?
As Ted Lasso said:
“Be curious. Not judgmental.”

.

.

.

What if leadership meant knowing what’s coming—and staying fearless anyway? ✨

When I asked @madhampatty.iswarya about the most powerful part of her father’s leadership, she didn’t talk about titles or speeches.
She spoke about presence. Intuition.
The way he senses what’s coming, prepares without panic, and leads without fear.
It’s not loud. It’s not flashy.
It’s leadership that grounds you—even when the world shifts.

🎧Watch this moment and more in her full episode on @therayaneshowpodcast . Now streaming.
